  <div class="section">
    <h3>Score Breakdown (0-100)</h3>
    <p style="font-size:13px;color:#9ca3af;margin-bottom:12px;">Each signal is scored across 6 categories. Higher = stronger setup.</p>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong style="color:#3b82f6;">Trend (0-20)</strong><br>EMA alignment, ADX trend strength, SMA direction. Tells you if the market is moving in a clear direction.</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong style="color:#10b981;">Momentum (0-20)</strong><br>RSI, MACD, Stochastic. Measures the speed and force of price movement.</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong style="color:#a78bfa;">Volume (0-20)</strong><br>Relative volume, VWAP, accumulation/distribution. Shows if smart money is behind the move.</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong style="color:#eab308;">Structure (0-20)</strong><br>Higher highs/lows, support/resistance, Bollinger position. Market structure shows the pattern.</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong style="color:#f97316;">Volatility (0-10)</strong><br>Bollinger squeeze, ATR, Keltner compression. Low vol before big moves = opportunity.</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong style="color:#ef4444;">Risk Quality (0-10)</strong><br>Clear stop levels, data quality, trend clarity. Better risk = safer trade.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h3>Market Regimes</h3>
    <p style="font-size:13px;color:#9ca3af;margin-bottom:12px;">The engine detects 5 market regimes. Different strategies work in different conditions.</p>
    <div class="journal-entry"><span class="regime-badge regime-trending">Trending</span><br>ADX > 25, clear direction. Best for: <strong>Trend Following, Momentum, Swing, Position</strong>.</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><span class="regime-badge regime-ranging">Ranging</span><br>Low ADX (5-15), no direction. Best for: <strong>Mean Reversion</strong>.</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><span class="regime-badge regime-compression">Compression</span><br>Bollinger squeeze active. Best for: <strong>Breakout, Scalping, Swing</strong>.</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><span class="regime-badge regime-volatile">Volatile</span><br>High ATR, wild swings. Best for: <strong>Scalping</strong>. Reduce leverage, wider stops.</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><span class="regime-badge regime-mixed">Mixed</span><br>No clear regime. Signals are weaker. Trade with caution or wait for clarity.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h3>7 Strategies</h3>
    <p style="font-size:13px;color:#9ca3af;margin-bottom:12px;">The engine runs all 7 strategies and picks the best for current conditions. The top 2-3 are shown on each signal card.</p>

    <div class="journal-entry">
      <strong style="color:#3b82f6;">Trend Following</strong>
      <span style="font-size:10px;color:#6b7280;margin-left:6px;">4H / 1D</span>
      <br>Rides established trends. Enters on pullbacks in the trend direction. Uses EMA alignment and ADX confirmation. Works best in <span class="regime-badge regime-trending" style="font-size:9px;">trending</span> regimes.
    </div>

    <div class="journal-entry">
      <strong style="color:#10b981;">Breakout</strong>
      <span style="font-size:10px;color:#6b7280;margin-left:6px;">1H</span>
      <br>Catches volatility expansion from compression zones. Looks for Bollinger squeeze + volume expansion + structure breakout. Best in <span class="regime-badge regime-compression" style="font-size:9px;">compression</span>.
    </div>

    <div class="journal-entry">
      <strong style="color:#eab308;">Mean Reversion</strong>
      <span style="font-size:10px;color:#6b7280;margin-left:6px;">1H</span>
      <br>Fades extremes back to average. Uses RSI oversold/overbought + VWAP + Bollinger band mean. Best in <span class="regime-badge regime-ranging" style="font-size:9px;">ranging</span> markets.
    </div>

    <div class="journal-entry">
      <strong style="color:#a78bfa;">Momentum</strong>
      <span style="font-size:10px;color:#6b7280;margin-left:6px;">1H</span>
      <br>Follows strong directional moves. Requires volume confirmation + MACD alignment. Best in <span class="regime-badge regime-trending" style="font-size:9px;">trending</span>.
    </div>

    <div class="journal-entry">
      <strong style="color:#ef4444;">Scalping</strong>
      <span style="font-size:10px;color:#6b7280;margin-left:6px;">15m / 1H</span>
      <br>Short-term: tight structure, quick momentum, volatility spikes. Uses 15-minute candles for fast entries and 1H for confirmation. Best in <span class="regime-badge regime-volatile" style="font-size:9px;">volatile</span> and <span class="regime-badge regime-compression" style="font-size:9px;">compression</span>. Targets are small but fast.
    </div>

    <div class="journal-entry">
      <strong style="color:#f97316;">Swing</strong>
      <span style="font-size:10px;color:#6b7280;margin-left:6px;">4H / 1D</span>
      <br>Multi-day holds. Focuses on higher-timeframe trend and structure. Enters on 4H pullbacks aligned with 1D direction. Best in <span class="regime-badge regime-trending" style="font-size:9px;">trending</span> and <span class="regime-badge regime-compression" style="font-size:9px;">compression</span>. Larger targets, wider stops.
    </div>

    <div class="journal-entry">
      <strong style="color:#06b6d4;">Position</strong>
      <span style="font-size:10px;color:#6b7280;margin-left:6px;">1D / 1W</span>
      <br>Long-term (weeks). Uses daily and weekly macro trends. Only trades with the big picture direction. Best in <span class="regime-badge regime-trending" style="font-size:9px;">trending</span>. Lowest leverage, widest stops, biggest targets.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h3>Timeframes (5 levels)</h3>
    <p style="font-size:13px;color:#9ca3af;margin-bottom:12px;">The engine analyzes candles across 5 timeframes to find confluence.</p>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>15m</strong> — Scalping setups, fast entries. 96 candles (24 hours of data).</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>1H</strong> — Core analysis timeframe (25% weight). 168 candles (7 days).</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>4H</strong> — Intermediate trend and structure (35% weight). 100 candles (~17 days).</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>1D</strong> — Daily trend, dominant weight (40%). 30 candles (1 month).</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>1W</strong> — Weekly macro trend for Position strategy. 26 candles (~6 months).</div>
    <div class="journal-entry" style="color:#6b7280;"><strong>Confluence</strong> — When 2/3 or 3/3 of the core timeframes (1H/4H/1D) agree on direction, the signal gets a confidence bonus. 3/3 = strong, 1/3 = weak.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h3>Key Indicators</h3>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>RSI (Relative Strength Index)</strong><br>Measures momentum. Below 30 = oversold (potential buy). Above 70 = overbought (potential sell). 14-period standard.</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>MACD</strong><br>Shows trend momentum. When MACD crosses above signal line = bullish. Histogram shows strength of the cross.</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>ADX</strong><br>Measures trend strength (not direction). Above 25 = trending. Above 40 = strong trend. Below 20 = no trend.</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>VWAP</strong><br>Volume Weighted Average Price. Institutions use this. Price above VWAP = bullish bias. Below = bearish.</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>Bollinger Bands</strong><br>Shows volatility. Price near lower band in uptrend = buy zone. Squeeze (narrow bands) = big move coming.</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>Stochastic</strong><br>Like RSI but compares price to range. K/D crossover in oversold = buy signal. In overbought = sell signal.</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>ATR (Average True Range)</strong><br>Measures volatility in price terms. Used to set stop losses and position sizes. Higher ATR = wider stops needed.</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>Market Structure</strong><br>HH/HL = bullish (higher highs + higher lows). LH/LL = bearish. Break of structure = potential reversal.</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>EMA (9/21)</strong><br>Fast/slow exponential moving averages. When 9 EMA crosses above 21 = bullish crossover. Price above both = uptrend.</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>SMA (20/50)</strong><br>Simple moving averages. 20 above 50 = bullish alignment. Price below both = downtrend.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h3>Risk Management Rules</h3>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>1. Never risk more than 2% per trade</strong><br>If your account is $10,000, max risk per trade = $200.</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>2. Always use a stop loss</strong><br>No exceptions. The system calculates stops using ATR + structure.</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>3. Risk/Reward minimum 1.5:1</strong><br>Your potential profit should be at least 1.5x your risk.</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>4. Leverage matches confidence</strong><br>Only use higher leverage when the score is 70+. High vol = low leverage.</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>5. 1 trade per pair</strong><br>Don't stack positions. Wait for your trade to close before opening another on the same pair.</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>6. Follow the system</strong><br>Journal shows you win more when you follow rules. Trust the process.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h3>Leverage Guide</h3>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>Score 80+</strong>: Up to 10x (very strong setup)</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>Score 70-79</strong>: Up to 7x (strong setup)</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>Score 60-69</strong>: Up to 5x (good setup)</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>Score 50-59</strong>: Up to 3x (moderate)</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>Score 40-49</strong>: Up to 2x (cautious)</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>Below 40</strong>: 1x only (weak setup, consider skipping)</div>
    <div class="journal-entry" style="color:#ef4444;"><strong>Volatile market?</strong> Cut leverage by 50%. Extreme vol? Use 1x only.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h3>Learning Engine</h3>
    <p style="font-size:13px;color:#9ca3af;margin-bottom:12px;">The app tracks every trade outcome and uses it to improve over time.</p>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>How it works</strong><br>Every closed trade is recorded with its strategy, regime, and result (win/loss + R:R). The learning engine adjusts strategy weights based on real performance. Those weights are now used live in the trading engine to score signals.</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>Weight adjustment</strong><br>Strategies with negative expectancy (losing over 20+ trades) get their scoring weights reduced by 5%. Strategies with positive expectancy (>0.5) get a 2% boost.</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>Regime tracking</strong><br>Wins and losses are broken down by market regime. Strategies need at least 5 trades before they can be selected in that regime (min-sample rule).</div>
    <div class="journal-entry" style="color:#3b82f6;"><strong>View it live:</strong> <a href="/learning" style="color:#3b82f6;">AI Engine</a> — strategy performance, weights, and regime stats.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h3>Quant-Desk Upgrades (v4)</h3>
    <p style="font-size:13px;color:#9ca3af;margin-bottom:12px;">21 upgrades for better signals and fewer losing trades.</p>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>Signals &amp; scoring</strong><br>1. Learned strategy weights used in scoring. 2. Min score (52) and confluence (2) gate – weak setups show HOLD. 3. BTC regime filter – no alt longs when BTC STRONG_SELL, no alt shorts when BTC STRONG_BUY. 4. MTF divergence penalty when 1H and 4H disagree. 5. Session filter – small score reduction outside 12–22 UTC. 6. Regime–strategy gating – e.g. no Mean Reversion in trending. 7. Min 5 trades per strategy before it can be selected.</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>Levels &amp; risk</strong><br>8. Dynamic ATR stops by regime (tighter in trending, wider in volatile). 9. Multi-timeframe S/R (1D/4H used for stops when available). 10. VWAP bands – bonus when price is in value zone (within 0.5 ATR of VWAP).</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>Execution &amp; position</strong><br>11. Trade buttons only when score ≥55 and confluence ≥2. 12. <strong>Multi-strategy trades</strong> – on each coin’s detail page you can open a trade using the main signal or any top strategy (Scalping, Momentum, Breakout, etc.) that scores ≥55; each strategy has its own stop and take-profit levels (scalping = tighter, swing/position = wider). 13. Trailing stop – stop moves to breakeven after 1R profit. 14. Slippage simulation (0.05%) on entry and exit. 15. Confidence-weighted position size (higher score = slightly larger size, cap 1.2×). 16. Cooldown – no same-direction re-entry on same coin for 4 hours after close.</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>Data &amp; learning</strong><br>16. Strategy weights from AI Engine feed back into signal scoring. 17. Expectancy and regime stats drive which strategies get selected. 18. Quality gate and session messages appear in “Why This Trade” when relevant.</div>
    <div class="journal-entry"><strong>Order blocks, FVG and liquidity clusters</strong><br>19. Order blocks – last opposing candle before a strong move (bullish OB = support, bearish OB = resistance); structure bonus when price is near a valid OB. 20. Fair value gaps (FVG) – 3-candle imbalances; price in or near a FVG zone adds confluence. 21. Liquidity clusters – swing highs/lows grouped by proximity; near a cluster adds structure context and appears in reasoning.</div>
